{"headline": "Today's Research Reports on Stocks to Watch: Advanced Micro Devices and NVIDIA Corporation - MarketWatch", "author": null, "tick": "NVDA", "link": "https://www.marketwatch.com/story/todays-research-reports-on-stocks-to-watch-advanced-micro-devices-and-nvidia-corporation-2018-02-02", "text": "Published: Feb 02, 2018 (ACCESSWIRE via COMTEX) -- NEW YORK, NY / ACCESSWIRE / February 2, 2018 / Shares of NVIDIA and AMD saw losses on Thursday after NVIDIA was removed from Goldman Sach's Conviction list on concerns about cryptocurrency volatility. RDI Initiates Coverage on: Advanced Micro Devices, Inc.   NVIDIA Corporation   Advanced Micro Devices, Inc. shares closed down 3.57% on Thursday with about 67.5 million shares traded. The company recently reported stronger than expected fourth quarter financial results which showed a 60% growth in revenue in its computer and graphics business. Revenue soared 34% in total to $1.48 billion. Full year revenue came in at $5.33 billion. The company's CEO Lisa Su said, \"2017 marked a key product and financial inflection point for AMD. Our newest wave of high-performance products and consistent execution created significant momentum for our business over the past year.\" So why the drop yesterday? Shares may be feeling the burn as its rival NVIDIA was removed from Goldman Sach's Conviction List because an analyst has cited concerns over the volatility of cryptocurrency. Access RDI's Advanced Micro Devices, Inc. Research Report at:   NVIDIA Corporation shares closed down 2.16% on Thursday on nearly 13 million shares traded. Traders showed some worry over Goldman Sachs removing the company from its conviction list. Analyst Toshiya Hari of the firm has removed the company from the list but has still maintained his \"buy\" rating on the stock and increased the price target to $281 from $228.. According to the analyst, \"Nvidia shares have simply come too far to warrant a spot on the Conviction List.\" He also cited concerns over NVIDIA's digital currency business. He wrote in a note to clients, \"While we continue to see meaningful upside to FY2019/2020 estimates and maintain our Buy rating, we believe a) the long-term secular growth angle in data center is now better understood and b) near-term dynamics in cryptocurrency demand may lead to increased earnings volatility.\" He also noted, \"While the increase in GPU demand from Ether miners is boosting fundamentals in the near-term, increased exposure to the Crypto market will, in our view, increase uncertainty and volatility, which are typically dilutive to valuation multiples.\" Shares of NVIDIA have gained 115 percent over the last 12 months. Access RDI's NVIDIA Corporation Research Report at:   Our Actionable Research on Advanced Micro Devices, Inc. and NVIDIA Corporation can be downloaded free of charge at Research Driven Investing. Research Driven Investing We are committed to providing relevant and actionable information for the self-directed investor. Our research is reputed for being a leader in trusted, in-depth analysis vital for informed strategic trading decisions. The nimble investor can leverage our analysis and collective expertise to execute a disciplined approach to stock selection. RDInvesting has not been compensated; directly or indirectly; for producing or publishing this document. Disclaimer: This article is written by an independent contributor of RDInvesting.com and Nadia Noorani, a CFA\u00ae charter holder, has provided necessary guidance in preparing the document templates. RDInvesting.com is neither a registered broker dealer nor a registered investment advisor. For more information please read our full disclaimer at . CONTACT For any questions, inquiries, or comments reach out to us directly at: Address: Research Driven Investing, Unit #901 511 Avenue of the Americas, New York, NY, 10011 Email: contact@rdinvesting.com CFA\u00ae and Chartered Financial Analyst\u00ae are registered trademarks owned by CFA Institu