's stock finished yesterday's session 2.08% lower at $7.05. A total volume of 3.18 million shares was traded, which was above their three months average volume of 3.12 million shares. The Company's shares have gained 0.86% in the last twelve months. The stock is trading below its 50-day moving average by 16.54. Furthermore, shares of SunPower, which researches, develops, manufactures, and delivers solar solutions worldwide, have an RSI of 33.41. Today's complimentary research report on SPWR is accessible at:     At the close of trading on Tuesday, shares in San Francisco, California headquartered Sunrun Inc. saw a decline of 1.07%, ending the day at $5.55. The stock recorded a trading volume of 1.59 million shares, which was higher than its three months average volume of 1.07 million shares. The stock is trading below its 50-day moving average by 7.10%. Moreover, shares of Sunrun, which engages in the design, development, installation, sale, ownership, and maintenance of residential solar energy systems in the US, have an RSI of 36.83. Sign up for free on Wall St. Equities and claim the latest report on RUN at:     Hayward, California headquartered Ultra Clean Holdings Inc.'s shares ended the day 1.03% higher at $19.65 with a total trading volume of 1.76 million shares, which was above their three months average of 1.40 million shares. The stock has gained 56.08% over the last twelve months. The Company's shares are trading below their 50-day moving average by 12.93%. Additionally, shares of Ultra Clean, which designs, develops, prototypes, engineers, manufactures, and tests production tools, modules, and subsystems for the semiconductor capital equipment and equipment industry segments primarily in North America, Asia, and Europe, have an RSI of 33.53. On January 18\n\t\t[th]\n\t, 2018, research firm Cowen upgraded the Company's stock rating from 'Market Perform' to 'Outperform', with a target price of $32 per share. See the free research coverage on UCTT at:      